ARTICLE.TITLE: Boy, 11, killed in St. Petersburg crash, police say
ARTICLE.TEXT:
ST. PETERSBURG — An 11-year-old boy was killed in a two-vehicle crash that took place Saturday, according to police.

Police did not say what time the crash took place, but sent out a statement at 11:20 p.m.

The crash took place at 15th Avenue S and 34th Street S.

Two adults and another child were also hurt in the collision. St. Petersburg police did not release any other information about the crash, but said the investigation is ongoing.
